To use the **Shared Resources** approach with the `maven-remote-resources-plugin`, you can package your `jib-nginx` and `jkube` folders into a JAR file and have all your projects automatically "pull" and use them.

This is the best way to share these folders if your projects are in different Git repositories or if you want to avoid duplicating these folders everywhere.

### Step 1: Create a "Resource Bundle" Project
Create a simple Maven project (e.g., `app-shared-resources`) to hold the common files.

**Directory Structure:**
```text
app-shared-resources/
├── pom.xml
└── src/
    └── main/
        └── resources/
            ├── jib-nginx/ (move your files here)
            └── jkube/     (move your files here)
```

**`pom.xml` for `app-shared-resources`:**
```xml
<project ...>
    <groupId>com.avangrid</groupId>
    <artifactId>app-shared-resources</artifactId>
    <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <!-- This plugin marks this JAR as a Resource Bundle -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-remote-resources-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.1.0</version>
                <executions>
                    <execution>
                        <goals>
                            <goal>bundle</goal>
                        </goals>
                    </execution>
                </executions>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>
</project>
```
*Run `mvn install` on this project to put it in your local/remote repository.*

---

### Step 2: Configure the Parent POM
In your **Parent POM**, add the configuration to "process" (unpack) these resources into every child project's `target` folder during the build.

**Parent `pom.xml` configuration:**
```xml
<build>
    <plugins>
        <!-- 1. Automatically fetch and unpack the shared folders -->
        <plugin>
            <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
            <artifactId>maven-remote-resources-plugin</artifactId>
            <version>3.1.0</version>
            <executions>
                <execution>
                    <goals>
                        <goal>process</goal>
                    </goals>
                    <configuration>
                        <resourceBundles>
                            <resourceBundle>com.avangrid:app-shared-resources:1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</resourceBundle>
                        </resourceBundles>
                    </configuration>
                </execution>
            </executions>
        </plugin>

        <!-- 2. Update Resources Plugin to use the UNPACKED files -->
        <plugin>
            <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
            <artifactId>maven-resources-plugin</artifactId>
            <executions>
                <execution>
                    <id>filter-jkube-resources</id>
                    <phase>process-resources</phase>
                    <goals><goal>copy-resources</goal></goals>
                    <configuration>
                        <outputDirectory>${project.build.directory}/jkube</outputDirectory>
                        <resources>
                            <resource>
                                <!-- Files are unpacked here by the remote-resources-plugin -->
                                <directory>${project.build.directory}/maven-shared-archive-resources/jkube</directory>
                                <filtering>true</filtering>
                            </resource>
                        </resources>
                    </configuration>
                </execution>
                <execution>
                    <id>filter-jib-nginx-resources</id>
                    <phase>process-resources</phase>
                    <goals><goal>copy-resources</goal></goals>
                    <configuration>
                        <outputDirectory>${project.build.directory}/jib-nginx</outputDirectory>
                        <resources>
                            <resource>
                                <directory>${project.build.directory}/maven-shared-archive-resources/jib-nginx</directory>
                                <filtering>true</filtering>
                            </resource>
                        </resources>
                    </configuration>
                </execution>
            </executions>
        </plugin>
    </build>
</build>
```

---

### Step 3: Use it in Child Projects
Your child projects now only need to extend the parent. They **no longer need** to have their own `jib-nginx` or `jkube` folders locally.

1.  **Delete** the `jib-nginx/` and `jkube/` folders from your child projects.
2.  **Add** the `<parent>` tag to the child `pom.xml`.
3.  When you run `mvn clean install` on the child, Maven will:
    *   Download the `app-shared-resources.jar`.
    *   Unpack it into `target/maven-shared-archive-resources/`.
    *   Filter and copy them to `target/jkube` and `target/jib-nginx`.
    *   Build your Jib image and Kubernetes manifests using these shared files.

### Why this is better:
*   **One Source of Truth**: If you need to change a Nginx configuration, you change it in `app-shared-resources` once, and every project gets the update.
*   **Clean Workspace**: No more duplicating the same deployment files across 10+ different repositories.
*   **Version Control**: You can version your shared resources (e.g., `1.0.0`, `1.1.0`) just like any other library.

