# To consolidate multiple similar projects into a parent-child relationship in Maven, you can extract all the common configurations (properties, profiles, and plugin setups) into a **Parent POM**.              
*****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************
*****************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************************

This will allow you to maintain the complex `jib-maven-plugin` and `kubernetes-maven-plugin` configurations in one place, while your individual projects only specify their unique metadata (`artifactId`, `name`, `description`).

### Step 1: Create the Parent Project

Create a new directory for your parent project (e.g., `app-spa-parent`) and create a `pom.xml` inside it. Use `pom` packaging.

#### Parent `pom.xml` Structure
Move all the common parts from your current `pom.xml` here:

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.avangrid</groupId>
    <artifactId>app-spa-parent</artifactId>
    <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
    <packaging>pom</packaging>

    <properties>
        <!-- Common Plugin Versions -->
        <node.version>v24.11.1</node.version>
        <npm.version>11.6.2</npm.version>
        <jib-maven-plugin.version>3.5.1</jib-maven-plugin.version>
        <kubernetes-maven-plugin.version>1.19.0</kubernetes-maven-plugin.version>
        <!-- ... add all other versions here ... -->

        <!-- Common Defaults -->
        <activeProfiles>dev,local</activeProfiles>
        <npm.build.script>build</npm.build.script>
        <jib-maven-plugin.image>${acr.server}/${project.artifactId}:${current.time}</jib-maven-plugin.image>
        <frontend.npmDownloadRoot>https://nexus.avangrid.net/repository/npm-registry/npm/-/</frontend.npmDownloadRoot>
        <frontend.nodeDownloadRoot>https://nodejs.org/dist/</frontend.nodeDownloadRoot>
    </properties>

    <profiles>
        <!-- Move all common profiles (local, dev, qat, stg, prod, os-windows, etc.) here -->
        <profile>
            <id>local</id>
            <properties>
                <jib-maven-plugin.image>${project.artifactId}:${current.time}</jib-maven-plugin.image>
                <opcoHostName>kubernetes.docker.internal</opcoHostName>
            </properties>
        </profile>
        <!-- ... other profiles ... -->
    </profiles>

    <build>
        <pluginManagement>
            <plugins>
                <!-- Move the complex plugin configurations here -->
                <plugin>
                    <groupId>com.google.cloud.tools</groupId>
                    <artifactId>jib-maven-plugin</artifactId>
                    <version>${jib-maven-plugin.version}</version>
                    <configuration>
                        <to>
                            <image>${jib-maven-plugin.image}</image>
                        </to>
                        <!-- Keep the entrypoint and common paths -->
                        <container>
                            <entrypoint>
                                <arg>nginx</arg>
                                <arg>-g</arg>
                                <arg>daemon off;</arg>
                            </entrypoint>
                        </container>
                        <extraDirectories>
                            <paths>
                                <path>
                                    <from>${project.basedir}/jib-nginx</from>
                                    <into>/etc/nginx/</into>
                                </path>
                                <path>
                                    <from>${project.build.directory}/dist/${project.artifactId}</from>
                                    <into>/usr/share/nginx/html/${service.context.path}</into>
                                </path>
                            </paths>
                        </extraDirectories>
                    </configuration>
                </plugin>

                <plugin>
                    <groupId>org.eclipse.jkube</groupId>
                    <artifactId>kubernetes-maven-plugin</artifactId>
                    <version>${kubernetes-maven-plugin.version}</version>
                    <configuration>
                        <namespace>${opcoNodeName}</namespace>
                        <!-- Common kubernetes resources config -->
                    </configuration>
                </plugin>
                <!-- ... other plugins (frontend, resources, spotless) ... -->
            </plugins>
        </pluginManagement>
    </build>
</project>
```

### Step 2: Handle Shared Folders (`jib-nginx` and `jkube`)

Since these folders are identical across projects, you have two options:

1.  **Multi-Module Approach (Recommended if projects are in the same repo):**
    Put the parent POM in the root and keep projects as sub-modules. You can reference the common folders via relative paths like `${project.parent.basedir}/common/jib-nginx`.
2.  **Shared Resources Plugin:**
    Create a small "resources" project that jars up the `jib-nginx` and `jkube` folders. Use the `maven-remote-resources-plugin` in your parent POM to automatically pull and unpack these into every project's `target` folder before the build.

### Step 3: Update Your Child Projects

Modify the `pom.xml` of your existing projects to extend the parent. They will now be very short.

#### Child `pom.xml` Example:
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<project ...>
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <parent>
        <groupId>com.avangrid</groupId>
        <artifactId>app-spa-parent</artifactId>
        <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
        <relativePath>../app-spa-parent/pom.xml</relativePath> <!-- Adjust path if needed -->
    </parent>

    <artifactId>app-spa-esco-web</artifactId>
    <name>ESCO Web App</name>
    <description>Frontend for ESCO</description>

    <properties>
        <!-- Only override unique properties -->
        <opcoNodeName>ibtxn</opcoNodeName>
        <opcoHostName>portal.ldev-nyseg.avangrid.us</opcoHostName>
        <service.context.path>escoweb</service.context.path>
        <service-name>${project.artifactId}</service-name>
    </properties>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <!-- Just list the plugins you want to activate; config is inherited -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>com.github.eirslett</groupId>
                <artifactId>frontend-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            </plugin>
            <plugin>
                <groupId>com.google.cloud.tools</groupId>
                <artifactId>jib-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            </plugin>
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.eclipse.jkube</groupId>
                <artifactId>kubernetes-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>
</project>
```

### Summary of Steps:
1.  **Create a Parent Project**: Set `<packaging>pom</packaging>`.
2.  **Centralize Properties**: Move all common `<version>` tags and `<properties>` to the parent.
3.  **Centralize Profiles**: Move the `<profiles>` section (dev, qat, prod, etc.) to the parent.
4.  **Use Plugin Management**: Move all complex `<plugin>` configurations to `<pluginManagement>` in the parent.
5.  **Simplify Children**: In each project, add the `<parent>` tag and delete all the duplicated code.
6.  **Parameterize**: Use variables like `${project.artifactId}` and `${service.context.path}` in the parent POM so it adapts to each child project automatically.

